<TITLE> HC stays ACC notice on Mahmudur Rahman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Tuesday stayed an order asking former energy adviser to provide information of his wealth. The bench of justices Nozrul Islam Chowdhury and Jahangir Hossain stayed a notice of the Anti-Corruption Commission by three months upon the petitioner's appeal. This notice, served on Apr 13 had asked Mahmudur Rahman, a former energy adviser of the BNP-led government, also acting editor of the daily Amar Desh, to provide information about the source of his wealth. The court also asked the Anti Corruption Commission to explain why the procedure of the notice should not be suspended. Rahman, on Apr 14, filed a petition with a lower court asking for a stay order on the notice. The appeal was rejected on Apr 21. Barrister Abdur Razzaque stood for the petitioner while advocate Khurshid Alam Khan fought for the ACC. bd
